# ==========================================
# CLOUDFLARE PAGES PROXY REWRITES (_redirects)
# ==========================================
# Cloudflare Pages is a static hosting provider and cannot execute the Node.js Express server.
# To route your backend API requests (/api/*) to your active Express backend:
# 
# OPTION A: Replace the URL below with your deployed production backend API endpoint.
#           Cloudflare Pages will proxy requests securely (returning HTTP 200).
# 
# OPTION B: Set the VITE_API_URL environment variable in your Cloudflare Pages dashboard 
#           or GitHub Actions secrets to point to your backend.
#
# Replace the placeholder URL with your actual backend:
/api/*  https://your-backend-server-endpoint.com/api/:splat  200
